</p>

<h2>Assemble your equipment and wash it</h2>

<p>
    You'll need to put your brew kettle and propane burner together. Follow the instructions with your
    propane burner to hook it up. It's pretty darn simple though. You should definitely check for gas
    leaks before starting to boil if you value your life and your house. I have included pictures below
    of me assembling my brew kettle. Finally, wash all of the equipment for brew day with odor-free,
    dye-free soap before you boil. It just arrived from the factory and you want to get any plastic or metal
    remnants off before brewing. You should do this again on subsequent brews to make sure everything
    is totally clean before sanitizing.
</p>

